records.descr: DE not competent to stand trial, case suspended

records.addlTxt: Court reporter Teri Groves. Defendant in court with Attorney Crystal A Vera.  Cecilia E DeMarco appeared for the State of Wisconsin. In court today for a competency hearing after a report from Dr. Schoenecker was submitted to the court stating the DE is not competent to proceed, but may be brought back to competency with treatment. State does not object to the finding. Atty Vera was unable to gain an answer from her client on whether or not her client agreed to the findings in the report. Court questioned the DE who objects to the finding. State calls Dr. Schoenecker to proceed to an evidentary hearing. Dr. Schoenecker is duly sworn and testifies. Direct by the State. Exhibit 1 is marked, offered and received. Atty Vera with cross exam. State with redirect. Court makes findings and finds the DE is not competent to proceed with this case, but could be brought back to competency with treatment. Court suspends the proceedings and commits the DE to DHS. Court to issue the orders for treatment.
